HEADWORD: establishmentarianism
<hw>es*tab`lish*men*ta"ri*an*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>the doctrine or political position that advocates establishment of
a church as the official state religion; -- applied especially to the
Church of England.</def>.⟦br⟧
